==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''{{Polytonic|Ἕλλην}}''' (''Hellen'') "Greek", "luminary, bright", from prefix '''{{Polytonic|ἑλ}}''' (''hel'') "sun, bright, shiny". (See [[helios]] "sun", [[electron]] "amber", etc.). In Greek mythology '''{{Polytonic|Ἕλλην}}''', whom the '''{{Polytonic|Ἕλληνες}}''' (''Hellenes'') "Greeks" were named after, 
was the son of '''{{Polytonic|Δευκαλίων}}''' (''Deucalion'') and '''{{Polytonic|Πύῤῥα}}''' (''Pyrrha'').

===Noun===
#An inhabitant, resident, or a person of descent from [[Hellas]], "Greece".
#Another word for [[Hellene]].

